  "title": "Admin & Invoicing ( Worker's Dormitory Administrator",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities</strong></u></p><p><strong>1. Administrative & Operations Management</strong></p><ul><li>Manage resident check-in, check-out, and room assignments.</li><li>Maintain up-to-date records of occupancy, bed availability, and resident information.</li><li>Handle issuance of access cards, keys, and ensure proper documentation.</li><li>Coordinate maintenance requests and follow up with technicians/contractors.</li><li>Conduct routine inspections of dormitory rooms and common areas.</li><li>Ensure compliance with MOM regulatory requirements for worker housing.</li><li>Assist in enforcing dormitory rules, safety protocols, and hygiene standards.</li></ul><p><strong>2. Invoicing & Finance Administration</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare monthly accommodation invoices for companies and tenants.</li><li>Track payments, reconcile accounts, and follow up on outstanding invoices.</li><li>Maintain organized financial records and support audit requirements.</li><li>Work closely with the finance department to ensure accurate billing.</li><li>Process deposits, refunds, and adjustments when necessary.</li></ul><p><strong>3. Resident Service & Support</strong></p><ul><li>Serve as the primary contact point for residents’ enquiries and issues.</li><li>Support new residents/wokers with onboarding information and orientation.</li><li>Assist in managing welfare programs, activities, and communication with employers.</li><li>Handle complaints professionally and escalate matters when needed.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or equivalent; relevant admin or facility operations experience preferred.</li><li>Experience in dormitory management, facility management, or accommodation admin is an advantage.</li><li>Strong organizational and multi-tasking skills.</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office (Excel, Word) or property/dorm management systems.</li><li>Good communication skills (English required; ability to speak Bengali, Tamil,or Mandarin is a plus.</li><li>Ability to handle resident issues professionally with empathy and firmness.</li></ul><p><strong>Work Conditions</strong></p><p>• May require shift work, weekend duty, or on-call support depending on dormitory operations.</p><p>• Fast-paced environment with frequent interaction with workers and employers.</p>",
